{
  "texts": [
    "Alignment with principles such as non-discrimination, fairness, benevolence, and non-maleficence is of utmost importance.",
    "In addition, the EU Guidelines for Trustworthy AI (European Commission 2019) require that the machine learning models being developed be always under human control and supervision, which means that any deviation from such principles should be addressed (or addressable).",
    "Therefore, alignment with ethical values may necessitate forgetting procedures aimed at identifying and eliminating sources of discriminatory or harmful behavior.",
    "In this section, we discuss the types of digital forgetting requests that can be found in previous surveys on general machine unlearning (Qu et al 2023; Xu et al 2023; Nguyen et al 2022; Shaik et al 2023).",
    "These surveys include forgetting requests for items, features/concepts, classes, and tasks."
  ]
}